<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-20T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-20T09:00:00-05:00" n="559" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d559">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/631: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-20T22:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">January
                                            20, 1919, 10 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received January 21, 6.16 a.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Is it your desire that I should inform the Chinese Government of the
                                terms of the agreement concerning Siberian and Chinese Eastern
                                Railway[s]? How will the invitation to appoint a member on the
                                railway commission be conveyed to the Chinese Government? The
                                Chinese have informally asked for information.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>